2 minutes (180°C). Allow to cool slightly (approx. 5-10 minutes), then use a cookie cutter (6 cm) to cut out biscuits (approx. 24). Set biscuits aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Mango and passionfruit"},{"content":"Place water, 200 g of the mango and 30 g of the sugar into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>, then cook <b>12 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add passionfruit pulp and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside to cool. Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk."},{"content":"Dice remaining 600 g of the mango flesh into small cubes (1-2 cm) and set aside."},{"content":" <strong>Re-insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place eggs and remaining 100 g of the sugar into mixing bowl and mix <b>6 min\/speed 4<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>."},{"content":"Add mascarpone and mix <b>30-40 sec\/speed 3<b>, or until mascarpone is combined."},{"content":"To assemble, dip reserved savoiardi biscuits into reserved cooled mango and passionfruit mixture to coat. Place 1 soaked biscuit into the bottom of 8 serving glasses, then cover each biscuit with 2 tablespoons of the mascarpone mixture. Top mascarpone mixture with fresh mango pieces. Repeat layering process until all ingredients have been used."},{"content":"Place glasses into refrigerator and leave to chill for at least 1 hour before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["All of the elements of this recipe can be made the day before however, it is best to assemble the dessert within 1-2 hours of serving to prevent the biscuits from becoming too soft."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h","8 portions"]}